The Telegraph - Calcutta
 313-run loss for SA
Colombo: Left-arm seamer Chaminda Vaas bowled a lethal spell to take six wickets on Sunday as Sri Lanka crushed South Africa by 313 runs in the second Test to clinch the series 1-0  their first-ever Test series win against the visitors. Chasing 493, the South Africans were dismissed for 179 on the final day. South Africa began the final day at 21 for two and Sri Lankas pacemen rattled their top-order in the morning session to leave the visitors struggling on 129 for five at lunch. (AP)  Copyright 
